The Tidemouth Dunes zone where Reach Warden and Harbor Warden jurisdictions overlap has been infiltrated by hostile elements exploiting the gap in authority. Tidemouth raiders are preying on caravans in the transition zone, rogue Outriders who have broken from the Red Sand Accounts are operating independently, and jurisdiction specters are disrupting legal-enforcement actions. The post commander requires the zone cleared before the formal jurisdictional boundary review can proceed.
The hostile elements in the Tidemouth jurisdiction overlap zone have been eliminated. Raiders, rogue Outriders, and jurisdiction specters have been cleared, and the Tidemouth Dunes are accessible for the formal boundary review. The post commander has submitted an enforcement sweep report to the Mafdet Harbor Authority as documentation supporting the proposed joint-jurisdiction compact.

